<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
3D Manhattan Chart Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>3D Manhattan Chart is three dimensional charting features. This feature enables the chart control to visualize data in three dimensional spaces (X axis, Y axis, and Z axis). 
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\3D Manhattan Chart Demo.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>


<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Render series in 3D space using View3DMode property.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Viewing the series in z axis.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>View Column, Bar, Area and Line Chart in 3D space.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The check box <Bold>"Allow 3D Rotate"</Bold> enables or disables the chart's Rotation when View 3D mode is set to true.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Chart Type"</Bold> to select the Type of the Series.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>
</FlowDocument>